<heading box="[604,1280,1170,1209]" centered="true" fontSize="12" level="2" pageId="10" pageNumber="53" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[604,967,1170,1209]" pageId="10" pageNumber="53">
Notioiaphria 
<taxonomicName authority="J. G. H. Loodt, 1977" authorityName="J. G. H. Loodt" authorityYear="1977" box="[831,967,1170,1209]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Notiolaphria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="africana" status="sp. n.">africana</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[984,1074,1171,1209]" pageId="10" pageNumber="53" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
<figureCitation box="[1095,1280,1171,1209]" captionStart="Figs 16-19" captionStartId="11.[297,356,2523,2556]" captionTargetBox="[306,1762,300,2479]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 16-19. Notiolaphria africana gen. et sp. n. (N.M. T2101) Holotype 0'. 16. Right wing. 17. Lateral aspect of head. 18-19. Genital bulb. 18. Lateral aspect. 19. Dorsal aspect (Note: Genital bulb, normally rotated through 180°, is drawn as ifunrotated) Abbreviations: A = aedeagus, C = clasper, E = epandrium, G = gonopod, H hypandrium, Pc = pseudoclasper. Pr = proctiger." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1472457/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="53">Figs 16-19</figureCitation>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[193,1688,1169,2595]" pageId="10" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis box="[200,378,1238,1275]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="53">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Similar to 
<emphasis box="[606,785,1238,1275]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="53">
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. G. H. Loodt" authorityYear="1977" baseAuthorityName="Bigot" baseAuthorityYear="1859" box="[606,780,1238,1275]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Notiolaphria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macra">N. macra</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Thoracic markings faint; microsetal distribution confined to distal half of wing only; gonopods of male narrowly rounded distally and lacking the finger-like projection characteristic of 
<emphasis box="[1188,1364,1338,1376]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="53">
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. G. H. Loodt" authorityYear="1977" baseAuthorityName="Bigot" baseAuthorityYear="1859" box="[1188,1359,1338,1376]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Notiolaphria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macra">N. macra</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[193,1688,1169,2595]" box="[202,866,1405,1443]" pageId="10" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis box="[202,406,1406,1443]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="53">Description:</emphasis>
Based on 3 6 3 pinned.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[193,1688,1169,2595]" pageId="10" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis box="[198,577,1472,1509]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="53">Holotype male: Head:</emphasis>
Lateral aspect (
<figureCitation box="[863,986,1471,1509]" captionStart="Figs 16-19" captionStartId="11.[297,356,2523,2556]" captionTargetBox="[306,1762,300,2479]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 16-19. Notiolaphria africana gen. et sp. n. (N.M. T2101) Holotype 0'. 16. Right wing. 17. Lateral aspect of head. 18-19. Genital bulb. 18. Lateral aspect. 19. Dorsal aspect (Note: Genital bulb, normally rotated through 180°, is drawn as ifunrotated) Abbreviations: A = aedeagus, C = clasper, E = epandrium, G = gonopod, H hypandrium, Pc = pseudoclasper. Pr = proctiger." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1472457/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="53">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
) similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. G. H. Loodt" authorityYear="1977" baseAuthorityName="Bigot" baseAuthorityYear="1859" box="[1190,1351,1471,1509]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Notiolaphria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macra">
<emphasis box="[1190,1351,1471,1509]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="53">N. macra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
except: Face more inflated; mystax composed of long black setae overlayed by numerous long, dorsoventrally flattened, shiny, gold setae. Proboscis as long as antenna.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[193,1688,1169,2595]" pageId="10" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis box="[198,333,1639,1676]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="53">Thorax:</emphasis>
Mesonotum and scutellum shiny black with a dark, greenish-blue, metallic appearance. Wing (
<figureCitation box="[544,671,1688,1726]" captionStart="Figs 16-19" captionStartId="11.[297,356,2523,2556]" captionTargetBox="[306,1762,300,2479]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 16-19. Notiolaphria africana gen. et sp. n. (N.M. T2101) Holotype 0'. 16. Right wing. 17. Lateral aspect of head. 18-19. Genital bulb. 18. Lateral aspect. 19. Dorsal aspect (Note: Genital bulb, normally rotated through 180°, is drawn as ifunrotated) Abbreviations: A = aedeagus, C = clasper, E = epandrium, G = gonopod, H hypandrium, Pc = pseudoclasper. Pr = proctiger." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1472457/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="53">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
) as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. G. H. Loodt" authorityYear="1977" baseAuthorityName="Bigot" baseAuthorityYear="1859" box="[804,969,1688,1726]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Notiolaphria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macra">
<emphasis box="[804,969,1688,1726]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="53">N. macra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but distribution of microsetae confined to distal half of wing.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[193,1688,1169,2595]" pageId="10" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis box="[197,369,1805,1842]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="53">Abdomen:</emphasis>
Terga and sterna shiny black with the same dark, greenish-blue, metallic appearance as the mesonotum and scutellum. Two long black macrosetae on T2, other terga lack lateral macrosetae. Genital bulb (
<figureCitation box="[1082,1272,1902,1940]" captionStart="Figs 16-19" captionStartId="11.[297,356,2523,2556]" captionTargetBox="[306,1762,300,2479]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 16-19. Notiolaphria africana gen. et sp. n. (N.M. T2101) Holotype 0'. 16. Right wing. 17. Lateral aspect of head. 18-19. Genital bulb. 18. Lateral aspect. 19. Dorsal aspect (Note: Genital bulb, normally rotated through 180°, is drawn as ifunrotated) Abbreviations: A = aedeagus, C = clasper, E = epandrium, G = gonopod, H hypandrium, Pc = pseudoclasper. Pr = proctiger." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1472457/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="53">Figs 18-19</figureCitation>
) elongate oval, rotated through 180°, claspers and pseudoclaspers as in 
<emphasis box="[1120,1307,1952,1990]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="53">
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. G. H. Loodt" authorityYear="1977" baseAuthorityName="Bigot" baseAuthorityYear="1859" box="[1120,1298,1952,1990]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Notiolaphria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macra">N. macra</taxonomicName>
;
</emphasis>
gonopods narrowly rounded distally and lacking the characteristic finger-like projections seen in 
<emphasis box="[1515,1683,2002,2040]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="53">
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. G. H. Loodt" authorityYear="1977" baseAuthorityName="Bigot" baseAuthorityYear="1859" box="[1515,1678,2002,2040]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Notiolaphria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macra">N. macra</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[193,1688,1169,2595]" pageId="10" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis box="[198,406,2069,2106]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="53">Dimensions:</emphasis>
Body length 9,3 mm; wing length 8,3 mm; width of head across eyes 3,6 mm; antenna length I, [mm; proboscis length 1,2 mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[193,1688,1169,2595]" pageId="10" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis box="[194,376,2185,2222]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="53">Paratypes:</emphasis>
2 6 3 Agree with holotype. Females have fewer and shorter gold setae in mystax. Dimensions: Body length 6 9,5-10,0 mm, 8,5-10,5 mm; wing length 6 7,5-8,0 mm, 7,5-8,5 mm.
</paragraph>
