<paragraph blockId="12.[209,1701,297,535]" pageId="12" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis box="[215,376,302,338]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="55">Remarks:</emphasis>
Oldroyd labelled the above specimens 'Stands in B.M. drawer 141 as 
<emphasis box="[213,419,351,387]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="55">coerulescens</emphasis>
Macq.? n. gen. et sp.?' As 
<emphasis box="[960,1166,351,387]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="55">coerulescens</emphasis>
was described as a species of 
<taxonomicName box="[209,342,400,436]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Laphria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[209,342,400,436]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="55">Laphria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and these specimens lack the characteristic laterally flattened proboscis of 
<taxonomicName box="[209,343,449,485]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Laphria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[209,343,449,485]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="55">Laphria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
there is no doubt that they are not 
<taxonomicName box="[948,1081,449,485]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Laphria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[948,1081,449,485]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="55">Laphria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<emphasis box="[1141,1528,447,485]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="55">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1851" box="[1141,1318,449,485]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Choerades" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Choerades</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[1336,1528,447,485]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Notiolaphria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ajricana">N. ajricana</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
possesses a genitalial form very similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. G. H. Loodt" authorityYear="1977" baseAuthorityName="Bigot" baseAuthorityYear="1859" box="[785,947,497,535]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Notiolaphria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macra">
<emphasis box="[785,947,497,535]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="55">N. macra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and clearly belongs to the same genus.
</paragraph>
